%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gen%20Z%20strikes%20back%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20hand%20being%20held%20out%20for%20a%20handshake%20while%20another%20hand%20appears%20to%20move%20away%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3bb211a227600e631ef12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20fall%2C%20a%20college%20junior%20I'll%20call%20Caleb%20received%20an%20offer%20for%20a%20summer%20internship%20with%20a%20midsize%20tech%20company.%20It%20wasn't%20his%20dream%20gig.%20But%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slump-professional-white-collar-jobs-recession-high-salary-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euncertain%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20computer-engineering%20majors%2C%20it%20was%20better%20than%20nothing.%20So%20he%20accepted%20it.%20Then%2C%20hoping%20to%20land%20something%20better%2C%20he%20kept%20applying%20to%20more%20internships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20spring%2C%20he%20got%20what%20he%20wanted%3A%20an%20internship%20that%20involved%20more%20interesting%20work%2C%20with%20a%20more%20established%20company%2C%20than%20the%20offer%20he%20had%20already%20accepted.%20But%20what%20to%20do%20about%20the%20first%20company%2C%20which%20was%20expecting%20him%20in%20a%20few%20months%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECaleb%20drafted%20a%20short%20email%20to%20the%20company's%20recruiter%2C%20thanking%20them%20for%20the%20opportunity%20but%20informing%20them%20that%20he%20was%20reneging%20on%20their%20offer.%20Before%20hitting%20send%2C%20he%20had%20a%20friend%20look%20it%20over%20to%20make%20sure%20it%20sounded%20professional.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20rude%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20response%20was%20terse%20%E2%80%94%20and%20angry.%20The%20recruiter%20admonished%20him%20for%20wasting%20everyone's%20time.%20A%20note%20about%20his%20betrayal%2C%20he%20was%20told%2C%20would%20be%20put%20on%20his%20%26quot%3Brecord.%26quot%3B%20Oh%2C%20and%20could%20he%20please%20inform%20them%20of%20where%20he%20would%20be%20working%20instead%3F%20Caleb%20didn't%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReneging%20has%20long%20been%20a%20dirty%20secret%20at%20university%20career%20centers%2C%20which%20work%20with%20students%20to%20help%20them%20land%20jobs.%20The%20long%20lag%20times%20between%20hiring%20in%20the%20fall%20and%20start%20dates%20in%20the%20summer%20have%20always%20led%20to%20some%20flip-flopping.%20But%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20students%20seem%20to%20be%20going%20back%20on%20their%20word%20with%20increasing%20ease.%20According%20to%20Veris%20Insights%2C%20an%20analytics%20and%20research%20firm%2C%20students%20reneged%20on%206%25%20of%20full-time%20offers%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20double%20the%20rate%20from%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20finding%20it%20to%20be%20more%20common%20over%20the%20past%20two%20or%20three%20cycles%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Laura%20Garcia%2C%20the%20director%20of%20undergraduate%20career%20education%20at%20Georgia%20Tech.%20%26quot%3BWe%20see%20more%20students%20that%20are%20moving%20around%20%E2%80%94%20accepting%20offers%2C%20then%20reneging%20and%20going%20with%20another%20offer.%20It's%20created%20some%20pretty%20difficult%20situations%20in%20terms%20of%20retaining%20certain%20employers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20easy%20to%20get%20riled%20up%20at%20students%20who%20break%20their%20promises%20to%20employers.%20But%20here's%20the%20thing%3A%20They%20know%20many%20companies%20are%20doing%20the%20exact%20same%20thing%20to%20students.%20They've%20heard%20about%20the%20rescinded%20offers%20from%20Amazon%2C%20Coinbase%2C%20and%20Meta%20that%20devastated%20college%20seniors%20the%20past%20two%20years.%20The%20logistics%20startup%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflexport-ceo-rescinds-job-offers-short-notice-hiring-freeze-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFlexport%3C%2Fa%3E%20revoked%20offers%20to%20new%20hires%20three%20days%20before%20they%20were%20set%20to%20start.%20And%20viral%20TikTok%20videos%20have%20given%20students%20a%20front-row%20seat%20to%20the%20impersonal%20way%20tech%20companies%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-firings-tech-hr-tiktok-cloudflare-employee-morale-bad-business-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaying%20off%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20a%20world%20in%20which%20employers%20don't%20keep%20their%20word%20to%20employees%2C%20students%20find%20nothing%20unethical%20about%20breaking%20their%20word%20in%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt-will%20employment%20goes%20both%20ways%2C%26quot%3B%20Caleb%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey%20should%20offer%20me%20a%20pension%20if%20they%20want%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloyalty%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20reneging%20is%20just%20the%20result%20of%20bad%20timing%3A%20Companies%20often%20require%20students%20to%20make%20commitments%20during%20the%20school%20year%20before%20they've%20finished%20interviewing%20with%20all%20prospective%20employers.%20But%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20students%20deliberately%20accept%20multiple%20offers%20and%20hoard%20them%20like%20a%20squirrel%20until%20right%20before%20their%20start%20date%20%E2%80%94%20just%20in%20case%20an%20employer%20reneges%20at%20the%20last%20minute.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20anxious%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-offer-revoked-rescinded-economy-recession-coinbase-redfin-meta-tech-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejobs%20will%20disappear%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Chelsea%20Schein%2C%20the%20senior%20director%20of%20university%20recruiting%20research%20at%20Veris%20Insights.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20gathering%20the%20jobs%20because%20they're%20scared%20if%20they%20don't.%26quot%3B%20Reneging%20isn't%20selfishness.%20It's%20a%20survival%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-boomers-low-employee-engagement-jobs-productivity-wfh-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Zers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20a%20new%20ethos%20about%20breaking%20their%20word%20to%20employers%2C%20which%20has%20always%20been%20considered%20taboo.%20Some%2044%25%20of%20students%20surveyed%20by%20Handshake%2C%20a%20job%20site%20for%20college%20students%2C%20said%20that%20accepting%20two%20offers%20is%20%26quot%3Breasonable%2C%26quot%3B%20up%20from%2035%25%20in%202022.%20And%20according%20to%20Veris%20Insights%2C%20only%206%25%20now%20say%20they%20would%20never%20renege%20on%20an%20offer%2C%20down%20from%2016%25%20in%202019.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20pretty%20common%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Caleb%2C%20whose%20friends%20also%20reneged%20on%20internships%20and%20full-time%20offers.%20%26quot%3BIt%20happens%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%2C%20when%20students%20renege%2C%20their%20universities%20pay%20the%20price.%20Leading%20employers%2C%20who%20don't%20like%20being%20jilted%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etrack%20renege%20rates%20by%20school%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20use%20those%20rates%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20continue%20recruiting%20at%20those%20schools.%20If%20a%20senior%20reneges%20on%20an%20offer%2C%20a%20sophomore%20may%20wind%20up%20having%20fewer%20employers%20to%20choose%20from.%20%26quot%3BHonor%20your%20commitment%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20pleads%20with%20students%20at%20Georgia%20Tech%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20other%20people%20don't%20get%20punished.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20job-search%20presentations%20she%20gives%2C%20Garcia%20tells%20students%20to%20imagine%20it's%20April%20of%20their%20senior%20year%2C%20and%20they%20get%20a%20call%20from%20the%20company%20that%20has%20hired%20them.%20%26quot%3BLaura%2C%20you're%20great%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20tells%20them.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20just%20met%20a%204.0%20student%20that%20had%20two%20more%20internships%20than%20you.%20I%20think%20I'm%20going%20to%20go%20with%20them.%20So%20I%20wish%20you%20well.%26quot%3B%20Can%20you%20imagine%20how%20furious%20you'd%20be%2C%20Garcia%20asks%20the%20students.%20You%20have%20to%20play%20by%20the%20rules%20if%20you%20want%20others%20to%20do%20the%20same.%20%26quot%3BI%20encourage%20students%20to%20stop%20thinking%20of%20corporations%20as%20just%20an%20entity%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUniversities%20are%20trying%20to%20fight%20the%20new%20norm%2C%20but%20there%20isn't%20much%20they%20can%20do%20about%20it.%20Many%20MBA%20programs%2C%20which%20are%20small%20enough%20to%20keep%20tabs%20on%20individual%20students%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etake%20a%20hard-line%20approach%3A%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Femployers.mbacareers.wharton.upenn.edu%2Frecruiting-policies%2F%234%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWharton%3C%2Fa%3E%20School%2C%20for%20example%2C%20notes%20the%20recruiting%20violation%20on%20a%20reneger's%20academic%20transcript%20and%20levies%20fines%20as%20high%20as%20%2420%2C000.%20But%20the%20typical%20punishment%20for%20most%20undergraduates%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20denying%20renegers%20access%20to%20services%20like%20university%20career%20fairs%20and%20job%20listings%20%E2%80%94%20is%20little%20more%20than%20a%20slap%20on%20the%20wrist.%20Students%20renege%2C%20in%20short%2C%20because%20they%20can%20get%20away%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20employers%20hate%20reneging%2C%20some%20acknowledge%20privately%20that%20they%20understand%20why%20so%20many%20students%20are%20doing%20it.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20just%20making%20a%20pragmatic%20decision%20for%20themselves%2C%20just%20like%20an%20employer%20would%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20a%20university%20recruiter%20at%20a%20large%20manufacturer.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20just%20kind%20of%20the%20reality.%20We%20both%20know%20now%20what%20game%20is%20being%20played.%26quot%3B%20If%20he%20were%20advising%20a%20young%20family%20member%20who%20accepted%20a%20job%20and%20then%20got%20a%20better%20offer%20from%20another%20employer%2C%20he%20admits%2C%20he%20would%20probably%20advise%20them%20to%20renege.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eemployers%20are%20doing%20everything%20they%20can%20to%20prevent%20students%20from%20reneging.%20They%20stay%20in%20regular%20touch%20with%20new%20hires%2C%20finding%20ways%20to%20keep%20them%20excited%20about%20the%20job.%20They%20connect%20them%20with%20a%20mentor%20before%20they%20start%2C%20to%20put%20a%20human%20face%20on%20the%20company.%20They%20encourage%20students%20to%20announce%20their%20new%20job%20on%20LinkedIn%20as%20soon%20as%20they%20accept%20the%20offer%20%E2%80%94%20to%20create%20some%20%26quot%3Bsocial%20accountability%2C%26quot%3B%20Schein%20says%2C%20and%20make%20it%20a%20little%20more%20awkward%20for%20them%20to%20change%20their%20minds.%20And%20if%20a%20student%20gets%20a%20better%20offer%2C%20companies%20sometimes%20sweeten%20the%20original%20deal%2C%20negotiating%20on%20things%20like%20the%20job's%20location%20and%20start%20date%20to%20keep%20the%20new%20hire%20from%20going%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20reneging%20is%20now%20so%20widespread%20that%20employers%20have%20taken%20to%20baking%20it%20into%20the%20hiring%20process.%20The%20recruiter%20at%20the%20large%20manufacturer%2C%20for%20example%2C%20says%20his%20company%20hands%20out%2010%25%20to%2015%25%20more%20offers%20than%20it%20expects%20to%20onboard%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20way%20airlines%20overbook%20their%20flights%2C%20assuming%20some%20passengers%20will%20wind%20up%20canceling.%20Among%20big%20employers%2C%20the%20practice%20is%20widespread%3A%20According%20to%20Veris%20Insights%2C%2059%25%20of%20companies%20with%20large%20university%20recruiting%20programs%20now%20overhire%2C%20so%20they're%20not%20left%20empty-handed%20when%20students%20renege.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20employers%2C%20though%2C%20not%20all%20reneging%20is%20equally%20bad.%20It's%20annoying%20when%20students%20back%20out%20early%20in%20the%20school%20year%2C%20leaving%20the%20company%20plenty%20of%20time%20to%20look%20for%20another%20candidate.%20It's%20a%20real%20headache%20when%20students%20renege%20in%20the%20spring%2C%20forcing%20recruiters%20to%20scramble%20for%20a%20replacement%20at%20the%20late%20minute.%20But%20it's%20downright%20unpardonable%20when%20students%20don't%20even%20bother%20to%20inform%20the%20company%20they've%20changed%20their%20mind%2C%20leaving%20HR%20departments%20puzzled%20as%20their%20onboarding%20calls%20and%20emails%20go%20unanswered.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20you%20get%20ghosted%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20the%20manufacturing%20recruiter.%20Schein%20even%20heard%20that%20a%20student%20had%20reneged%20after%20receiving%20a%20signing%20bonus%20%E2%80%94%20and%20didn't%20return%20the%20money.%20It's%20not%20just%20whether%20you%20renege%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20how%20you%20do%20it%20that%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchein%2C%20who%20also%20teaches%20undergraduates%20at%20Wharton%2C%20likens%20the%20job%20decisions%20her%20students%20face%20to%20their%20love%20lives.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20make%20a%20commitment%20to%20a%20romantic%20partner%2C%20you%20want%20to%20stick%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20it's%20not%20right%20for%20you%2C%20there's%20an%20obligation%20to%20yourself%20and%20your%20growth.%20I've%20mentored%20my%20own%20students%20on%20reneging%20in%20a%20way%20that%20respects%20the%20process%20and%20respects%20the%20recruiters.%20Everyone%20feels%20like%20they're%20better%20off%2C%20because%20the%20student%20found%20the%20right%20home%20for%20them%20professionally.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECaleb%20is%20currently%20enjoying%20the%20summer%20internship%20with%20the%20company%20he%20chose%20over%20the%20initial%20offer%20he%20accepted.%20When%20that%20wraps%20up%20in%20the%20next%20few%20weeks%2C%20he'll%20start%20applying%20to%20full-time%20roles%20for%20when%20he%20graduates%20in%202025.%20His%20plan%20is%20to%20apply%20to%2020%20to%2030%20companies.%20He's%20already%20researched%20them%20extensively%20%E2%80%94%20looking%20up%20not%20only%20their%20salary%20data%20but%20also%20their%20reputations%20as%20an%20employer%20and%20whether%20they've%20imposed%20any%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-jobs-recession-layoffs-gen-z-students-class-of-2023-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20wants%20to%20land%20a%20role%20with%20job%20security%2C%20a%20competitive%20salary%2C%20good%20retirement%20benefits%2C%20and%20work%20assignments%20that%20will%20get%20his%20career%20off%20to%20a%20good%20start.%20If%20he%20accepts%20one%20offer%2C%20only%20to%20get%20a%20better%20one%20down%20the%20road%2C%20he%20says%20he's%20absolutely%20prepared%20to%20renege%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20my%20first%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20determines%20so%20much%20of%20my%20career%20trajectory.%20It's%20not%20something%20you%20should%20play%20around%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-college-students-renege-job-offers-tech-rescinded-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722245822000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3bb411a227600e631ef2b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22or