country.%20After%20graduating%2C%20I%20accepted%20a%20position%20with%20ARM%20in%20Cambridge.%20I've%20lived%20and%20worked%20in%20the%20UK%20for%20the%20last%2015%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20in%20engineering%20roles%20but%20soon%20realized%20my%20passion%20for%20technology%20and%20storytelling%2C%20which%20drove%20me%20toward%20marketing%20communications.%20This%20transition%20wasn't%20financially%20motivated%20but%20about%20finding%20joy%20in%20my%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEntering%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-rising-stars-in-public-relations-in-2024-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPR%20and%20marketing%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20with%20a%20learning%20curve.%20My%20roles%20often%20involved%20bridging%20the%20gap%20between%20engineers%2C%20scientists%2C%20and%20journalists%2C%20leveraging%20my%20technical%20background%20and%20communication%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc52ef30-31dc-48a3-adef-a46f4e9d2c9e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20joined%20Meta%20because%20of%20its%20impact%20and%20scale%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20I%20left%20my%20role%20as%20head%20of%20technology%20PR%20and%20communications%20at%20Ocado%20Group%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-hiring-strategy-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoined%20Meta%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20seeing%20a%20role%20that%20interested%20me%20on%20LinkedIn.%20I%20started%20interfacing%20with%20teams%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20clear%20about%20what%20I%20wanted%20regarding%20salary%20and%20benefits%2C%20including%20stock%20options.%20Meta%20offered%20me%20a%20comprehensive%20benefits%20package%20that%20met%20my%20expectations.%20It%20included%20healthcare%2C%20parental%20leave%2C%20gym%20memberships%2C%20and%20a%20pension%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20offered%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-offering-massive-signing-bonuses-to-combat-labor-crisis-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esign-on%20bonus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20my%20compensation%20included%20a%20yearly%20bonus%2C%20half%20based%20on%20my%20performance%20and%20half%20on%20the%20company's%20financial%20performance.%20The%20percentage%20increased%20with%20promotions%2C%20starting%20at%2020%25%20and%20moving%20to%2025%25%20as%20I%20advanced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20I%20left%20in%202022%2C%20I%20was%20making%20%C2%A3135K%2C%20around%20%24173%2C000%2C%20in%20base%20salary%20and%20%C2%A3190K%20in%20total%2C%20around%20%24244%2C000%2C%20including%20the%20bonus%20and%20RSUs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22379a3d3f-6755-4ba3-b048-4063dc67f6f8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETo%20get%20promoted%20at%20Meta%2C%20you%20need%20to%20perform%20and%20collaborate%20effectively%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20promotion%20process%20at%20Meta%20involved%20a%20twice-a-year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-managers-make-during-performance-reviews-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformance%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20cycle.%20Promotions%20were%20about%20individual%20achievements%20and%20how%20collaboratively%20and%20effectively%20you%20worked%20with%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20sometimes%20feels%20like%20navigating%20social%20dynamics%2C%20as%20building%20positive%20relationships%20is%20crucial.%20I%20was%20promoted%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20other%20companies%20I've%20worked%20for%2C%20decision-making%20was%20mainly%20driven%20from%20the%20top%2C%20and%20teams%20had%20clear%20areas%20of%20focus%2C%20which%20they%20rarely%20strayed%20away%20from.%20Meta%20was%20unique%20because%20decision-making%20was%20also%20done%20cross-functionally%2C%20spanning%20multiple%20teams%2C%20which%20meant%20you%20could%20leverage%20the%20expertise%20of%20people%20outside%20your%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f5d087f5-b862-4478-84f3-0ccc7b4a462b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20size%20of%20Meta%20was%20a%20new%20experience%20for%20me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20size%20was%20unlike%20any%20I%20had%20worked%20at%20before.%20The%20vast%20scale%20introduced%20challenges%20and%20opportunities%20unique%20to%20a%20global%20company%20with%20significant%20societal%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-median-yearly-pay-employee-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta's%20large%20scale%3C%2Fa%3E%20meant%20initiating%20projects%20was%20more%20complex%20than%20in%20smaller%20companies.%20Projects%20required%20buy-in%20from%20cross-functional%20teams%20and%20sometimes%20had%20to%20pass%20through%20several%20layers%20of%20approval%2C%20which%2C%20while%20thorough%2C%20could%20slow%20down%20the%20process.%20There%20would%20be%20times%20when%20you'd%20have%20dozens%20of%20people%20involved%20in%20a%20decision%20or%20project%20that%20shouldn't%20have%20required%20much%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20prominence%20also%20meant%20that%20the%20media%20and%20the%20public%20constantly%20scrutinized%20our%20work%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20for%20a%20company%20with%20such%20a%20broad%20societal%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b73c3ce0-e00b-4c22-87da-0f0f2f884ffd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20are%20advantages%20and%20disadvantages%20of%20being%20associated%20with%20such%20an%20impactful%20company%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20name%20recognition%20and%20validation%20of%20my%20experience%20provided%20a%20competitive%20edge%20when%20seeking%20jobs%2C%20which%20I%20started%20to%20do%20after%20I%20had%20been%20at%20Meta%20for%20around%203%20%C2%BD%20years.%20This%20part%20of%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20often%20caught%20the%20attention%20of%20recruiters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20also%20some%20drawbacks.%20Smaller%20companies%20might%20hesitate%20to%20hire%20someone%20from%20a%20major%20tech%20firm%20due%20to%20concerns%20about%20matching%20