a%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20decided%20to%20move%20to%20Delhi%20to%20her%20father%E2%80%99s%20place%20in%20search%20of%20work.%20With%20only%20Rs%20500%20in%20her%20pocket%2C%20she%20relocated%20to%20the%20city%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20their%20three%20young%20children.%20%E2%80%9CI%20looked%20for%20jobs%2C%20but%20without%20any%20formal%20education%2C%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20find%20work.%20My%20husband%20also%20struggled%20to%20find%20employment.%20After%20two%20months%2C%20we%20began%20working%20on%20a%20field%20through%20sharecropping%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharecropping%20is%20a%20legal%20arrangement%20where%20a%20landowner%20permits%20a%20tenant%20to%20cultivate%20their%20land%2C%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20crops%20produced.%20The%20five-member%20family%20began%20living%20in%20a%20small%20room%20on%20the%20field.%20They%20spent%20their%20days%20cultivating%20vegetables%2C%20but%20the%20income%20from%20their%20efforts%20was%20insufficient%20to%20sustain%20them.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20price%20of%20vegetables%20in%20the%20market%20would%20fluctuate%20and%20we%20would%20hardly%20earn%20any%20profits%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%2055-year-old.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpickles-2_11zon-1722235303.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Starting%20with%20karonda%20(black%20currants)%2C%20she%20introduced%20a%20variety%20of%20pickles%2C%20including%20mangoes%2C%20chillies%2C%20and%20lemons.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpickles-2_11zon-1722235303.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpickles-2_11zon-1722235303-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpickles-2_11zon-1722235303-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpickles-2_11zon-1722235303-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpickles-2_11zon-1722235303-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-358852%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EStarting%20with%20%3Cem%3Ekaronda%20%3C%2Fem%3E(black%20currants)%2C%20Krishna%20introduced%20a%20variety%20of%20pickles%2C%20including%20mangoes%2C%20chillies%2C%20and%20lemons.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20turning%20point%20came%20in%20Krishna%E2%80%99s%20life%20when%20she%20heard%20about%20a%20training%20programme%20on%20value%20addition%20of%20post-harvest%20losses%20through%20a%20television%20programme.%20She%20enrolled%20in%20a%20course%20at%20Krishi%20Vigyan%20Kendra%20(KVK)%2C%20where%20she%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F342261%2Fwoman-entrepreneur-saroj-prajapati-founder-moms-magic-pickle-mango-madhya-pradesh%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAmit%2520tells%2520The%2520Better%2520India%2Ctastes%2520it%2520becomes%2520a%2520fan.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emastered%20the%20art%20and%20science%20of%20making%20pickles%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Emurabba%3C%2Fem%3E%20(marmalade).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20marked%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20new%20path%20for%20her%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20Rs%20500%20to%20Rs%205%20crore%20empire%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20an%20enthused%20student%2C%20Krishna%20would%20set%20out%20to%20the%20training%20centre%20with%20post-harvest%20losses%2C%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3Ekaronda%20%3C%2Fem%3E(black%20currants)%20from%20her%20field%2C%20a%20few%20spices%2C%20salt%2C%20and%20utensils.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAlthough%20I%20grew%20up%20seeing%20my%20%3Cem%3Edadi%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Enani%20%3C%2Fem%3E(grandmothers)%20make%20pickles%2C%20the%20know-how%20that%20I%20learnt%20in%20the%20training%20was%20insightful.%20As%20homemakers%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20really%20calculate%20the%20amounts%20of%20spices%20and%20salt%20to%20be%20added%20to%20the%20pickle.%20However%2C%20I%20was%20taught%20ways%20to%20enhance%20the%20taste%20as%20well%20as%20the%20shelf%20life%20of%20pickles%20naturally.%20The%20key%20was%20the%20measurement%20of%20spices%20and%20oils%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20Krishna%20started%20making%20the%20pickles%2C%20but%20she%20had%20little%20knowledge%20of%20commercialising%20the%20products.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20set%20up%20a%20small%20table%20on%20the%20roadside%20and%20put%20our%20products%20on%20display.%20It%20was%20not%20a%20very%20busy%20road%20but%20we%20wanted%20to%20attract%20people%20to%20our%20stall.%20So%2C%20we%20placed%20two%20large%20earthen%20pots%20of%20water%20along%20with%20the%20pickles.%20I%20offered%20pickles%20as%20samples%20to%20those%20who%20stopped%20to%20drink%20free%20water%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20simple%20yet%20effective%20strategy%20slowly%20built%20her%20customer%20base.%20She%20also%20started%20participating%20in%20local%20fairs%20to%20promote%20the%20products.%20Over%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20her%20pickles%20grew%2C%20allowing%20her%20to%20formally%20launch%20her%20company%20%E2%80%98Shri%20Krishna%20Pickles%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20eventually%20open%20her%20own%20factory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20with%20%3Cem%3Ekaronda%20%3C%2Fem%3E(black%20currants)%2C%20she%20introduced%20a%20variety%20of%20pickles%2C%20including%20mangoes%2C%20chillies%2C%20and%20lemons.%20Today%2C%20she%20offers%20over%20250%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F300822%2Fsenior-citizen-entrepreneur-sheila-pickles-jams-traditional-kerala-recipes-home-business-