arents-south-korea-seoul-750-per-month-population-declines-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20allowance%20system%20for%20parents%20with%20newborns%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%2C%20in%20a%20way%20more%20radical%20proposals%2C%20are%20probably%20a%20result%20of%20policymakers%20feeling%20this%20sense%20of%20desperation%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffaculty.smu.edu.sg%2Fprofile%2Fpaulin-tay-straughan-1431%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPaulin%20Straughan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20sociology%20professor%20at%20the%20Singapore%20Management%20University%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAll%20the%20traditional%20ideas%20that%20we%20had%20don't%20seem%20to%20work.%20So%20we%20have%20to%20try%20more%20novel%20ideas%20to%20push%20the%20needle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flkyspp.nus.edu.sg%2Four-people%2Ffaculty%2Ftan-poh-lin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPoh%20Lin%20Tan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20senior%20research%20fellow%20at%20Singapore's%20Institute%20of%20Policy%20Studies%2C%20says%20there%20still%20could%20be%20some%20value%20in%20rolling%20out%20micro-interventions%20like%20Tokyo's%20and%20Korea's%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20may%20actually%20be%20rational%20to%20pursue%20policies%20at%20the%20fringe%2C%20due%20to%20the%20high%20difficulty%20of%20engineering%20the%20societal%20change%20that%20addresses%20root%20causes%2C%20and%20instead%20look%20for%20low-hanging%20fruit%20in%20the%20form%20of%20low-cost%20interventions%20that%20can%20make%20a%20difference%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECountries%20who%20find%20themselves%20turned%20off%20by%20the%20financially%20onerous%20policies%20implemented%20by%20Nordic%20countries%20like%20Sweden%20and%20Finland%20%E2%80%94%20including%20heavily%20subsidized%20childcare%20and%20housing%20allowances%20%E2%80%94%20may%20want%20to%20score%20a%20bigger%20bang%20for%20their%20buck%20through%20one-off%20handouts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20as%20radical%20as%20making%20a%20dating%20app.%20Countries%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.madeforfamilies.gov.sg%2Fsupport-measures%2Fraising-your-child%2Ffinancial-support%2Fbaby-bonus-scheme%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESingapore%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fhong-kong%2Fsociety%2Farticle%2F3264045%2Fhong-kong-gives-out-hk35-million-baby-bonuses-experts-say-raising-birth-rate-requires-policy-rethink%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHong%20Kong%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20given%20families%20cash%20bonuses%20when%20they%20welcome%20a%20newborn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Singapore%2C%20parents%20can%20receive%20%2411%2C000%20each%20for%20their%20first%20and%20second%20child%20and%20%2413%2C000%20for%20each%20subsequent%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20such%20measures%20do%20not%20seem%20to%20appeal%20to%20young%20women%20like%20Lee%2C%20who%20believe%20that%20having%20a%20child%20is%20a%20big%20commitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vanessa%20Lee%20(left)%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20Jonas%20Hue%20(right)%2C%20both%2028.%20The%20couple%20got%20married%20in%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667920eb40cf2af6e4f4e46a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22427%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVanessa%20Lee%20(left)%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20Jonas%20Hue%20(right)%2C%20both%2028.%20The%20couple%20married%20in%202023.%3Cp%3EVanessa%20Lee%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELee%2C%20who%20owns%20two%20dogs%20and%20a%20cat%2C%20said%20that%20governments%20may%20be%20overestimating%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20one-off%20interventions%20in%20bolstering%20birth%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSure%2C%20you%20can%20get%20more%20people%20to%20get%20married%2C%20and%20then%20the%20chances%20of%20people%20having%20kids%20maybe%20will%20increase%20a%20little%20bit.%20But%20I%20think%20unless%20you%20solve%20the%20main%20issue%20of%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20parents%20to%20care%20for%20their%20kids%20sustainably%2C%20it%20will%20still%20be%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20a%20shift%20in%20societal%20mindsets%20toward%20work%20and%20family%20needs%20to%20occur%20for%20her%20peers%20to%20consider%20having%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20about%20popping%20a%20kid%20out.%20It's%20about%20becoming%20a%20parent%20and%20thinking%20long%20term%20%E2%80%94%20how%20will%20I%20take%20care%20of%20the%20kid%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20would-be%20parents%20are%20put%20off%20by%20the%20financial%20costs%20of%20starting%20a%20family%2C%20which%20aren't%20solved%20by%20one-off%20baby%20bonuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20choose%20to%20spend%20a%20part%20of%20my%20income%20on%20children%20because%20it's%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20content%20creator%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-china-not-having-kids-tell-us-why-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEmily%20Huang%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2029%2C%20told%20BI%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20thing%20on%20my%20mind%20right%20now%20is%20how%20I%20am%20going%20to%20fund%20my%20retirement.%20I%20feel%20like%20with%20my%20current%20income%20level%2C%20I%20can't%20retire%20comfortably%20anytime%20soon%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2234e2b598-f664-4326-89db-9a50f3b91029%5C%22%3EGovernments%20need%20to%20rethink%20their%20approach%20to%20the%20demographic%20crisis%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20that%20BI%20spoke%20to%20said%20that%20while%20the%20measures%20may%20be%20well-meaning%2C%20they%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthrowing-money-schemes-wont-solve-global-fertility-crisis-demography-experts-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunlikely%20to%20reverse%20their%20countries'%20demographic%20trajectory%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiems.ust.hk%2Fpeople%2Ffaculty-associates%2Fgietel-basten-stuart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStuart%20Gietel-Basten%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20social%20science%20and%20public%20policy%20professor%20at%20the%20Hong%20Kong%20University%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology%2C%20said%20that%20governments%20are%20tackling%20the%20%26quot%3Bwrong%20problem%26quot%3B%20if%20they%20think%20that%20low%20birth%20rates%20are%20simply%20due%20to%20people%20not%20having%20sex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20it's%20the%20wrong%20problem.%20Most%20people%20in%20order%20to%20have%20children%20have%20sex%2C%20that%20is%20true.%20But%20it%20also%20doesn't%20guarantee%20that%20having%20sex%20brings%20children%20and%20that%20not%20having%20sex%20is%20the%20only%20reason%20why%20people%20are%20not%20having%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20Gietel-Basten%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20plenty%20of%20policies%20which%20have%20been%20designed%20to%20increase%20birth%20rates%2C%20and%20there%20is%20very%20little%2C%20if%20hardly%20any%2C%20evidence%20at%20all%20to%20show%20that%20these%20policies%20have%20worked%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESMU's%20Straughan%20said%20that%20countries%20would%20be%20better%20off%20trying%20to%20realize%20the%20potential%20of%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-retirement-crisis-pensions-aging-population-social-security-workforce-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaging%20and%20graying%20populations%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%2C%20we%20have%20to%20accept%20that%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20greater%20proportion%20of%20people%20who%20want%20to%20stay%20single.%20That's%20okay%2C%26quot%3B%20Straughan%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20concurrently%2C%20we%20then%20have%20to%20say%2C%20if%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20more%20seniors%20now%2C%20then%20what%20do%20we%20need%20to%20do%20differently%20in%20order%20to%20maximize%20their%20potential%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20more%20seniors%2C%20Straughan%20said%2C%20need%20not%20be%20a%20bad%20thing%20for%20societies.%20They%20can%20still%20contribute%20to%20society%20as%20volunteers%2C%20even%20after%20retirement%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20governments%20should%20not%20brush%20aside%20their%20dwindling%20fertility%20rates%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELow%20birth%20rates%2C%20according%20to%20HKUST's%20Gietel-Basten%2C%20are%20a%20%26quot%3Bbarometer%20of%20the%20challenges%20in%20society%26quot%3B%20and%20should%20thus%20be%20seen%20as%20%26quot%3Bsymptoms%20of%20problems%20in%20a%20society.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20hectoring%20and%20bullying%20young%20people%20into%20having%20more%20children%20is%20not%20the%20answer%2C%20right%3F%20Because%20people%20don't%20have%20children%20for%20the%20state%2C%20and%20people%20certainly%20don't%20have%20children%20to%20save%20a%20pension%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20listen%20to%20young%20families%20and%20genuinely%20try%20to%20support%20them.%20And%20until%20that%20happens%2C%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20get%20anywhere%20by%20coming%20up%20with%20funny%20ideas%20and%20imposing%20them%20in%20a%20top-down%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasia-governments-have-their-birth-rate-boosting-tactics-all-wrong-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722218450000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66753575423319f0c3723d9c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasia-governments-have-their-birth-rate-boosting-tactics-all-wrong-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20expert%20told%20BI%20that%20there%20is%20%26quot%3Bvery%20little%2C%20if%20hard%20any%20evidence%20at